      "content": "it's not just \"a moment\" though. it feels permanent. like the version of me that actually cared and had the drive is just gone. i look at my desk and see all this work and i just feel... nothing. i feel like i'm just a ghost in my own life at this point. everything is just so loud and stressful, and i'm just so incredibly weary of the constant struggle just to stay afloat. i just want peace. i just want to not have to feel this pressure anymore.",
